        <odd id="ref7">
            <head>General note</head>
            <p>For a biography on James Lick, see Rosemary Lick, "The Generous Miser" (Ward Ritchie Press, 1967).</p>
        </odd>
        <bioghist id="ref5">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Thomas E. Fraser was the foreman at the Lick Homestead, home of James Lick (1796-1876) in San Jose. He was in charge, with Trustee Captain Richard S. Floyd, of the construction of the Lick Observatory, then the most powerful telescope in the world.</p>
        </bioghist>
